.SH NAME
makrounaDB \- Redis\-inspired in\-memory database server with RESP2
support
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]makrounaDB\f[R] [\f[B]\[en]port\f[R] \f[I]PORT\f[R]]
[\f[B]\[en]aof\f[R] \f[I]PATH\f[R]] [\f[B]\[en]no\-banner\f[R]]
.PP
\f[B]makrounaDB\f[R] \f[B]\[en]nl\-shell\f[R] [\f[B]\[en]host\f[R]
\f[I]IP\f[R]] [\f[B]\[en]port\f[R] \f[I]PORT\f[R]]
.PP
\f[B]makrounaDB\f[R] [\f[B]\-h\f[R]|\f[B]\[en]help\f[R]]
.SH DESCRIPTION
\f[CR]makrounaDB\f[R] is a lightweight, Redis\-inspired database server
written in modern C++.
It supports RESP2\-style requests, string key/value operations, key
expiration (TTL), and append\-only file persistence (AOF).
